      "side": 1,
      "message": "Seems like there’s going to be a transition somewhere. As you point out, it’s hard to imagine the Windows API changing in such a way that uint32_t, DWORD, and UINT aren’t all really unsigned int. At least I don’t see that happening without invalidating just about everything that we or anyone else has ever written.\n\nIf you want to be extra-paranoid, you could static_assert for type equivalence at the point of “conversion,” but that’s quite likely overkill.\n\nI personally thought that the status quo made more sense given your subsequent findings and my next comment. But I’m OK with either.\n\n(P.S. Do you ever envision when you write something like “that’d be overkill” that a future version of yourself will some day find himself working on a really hard bug that would have been caught by the thing you’re arguing against today?)",
